libvorbis (Xiph.Org Foundation)
-------------------------------

The 256-entry floor1 inverse-dB lookup table in `src/dbtable.rs`
(`FLOOR1_INVERSE_DB`) is reproduced verbatim from the Vorbis I
reference implementation (libvorbis, file `lib/lookups.c`, constant
`FLOOR_fromdB_LOOKUP`). The table is required for bit-exact decoder
output compatibility with the reference.

The pre-baked reference setup packet bytes in
`src/libvorbis_setup.rs` (`LIBVORBIS_SETUP_MONO_48K_Q3`) were produced
by running `ffmpeg -c:a libvorbis -q:a 3` and extracting the setup
header from the resulting Ogg stream.

Algorithms in `src/codebook.rs` (marker-based Huffman construction,
cf. libvorbis `lib/sharedbook.c` `_make_words`) and `src/floor.rs`
(floor1 inverse rendering, cf. libvorbis `lib/floor1.c`
`floor1_inverse2`) are independent Rust re-implementations of the
algorithms described in the Vorbis I specification, cross-checked
against libvorbis for bit-exact conformance. They do not reproduce
libvorbis source code but are listed here for completeness.

